# Coding standards

Inspired by [agents.md](https://agents.md/), [Clean Code](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2012/08/13/the-clean-architecture.html) (Robert C. Martin), and pragmatic JS style guides.

## Language

- **English only** in `.js`, `.html` placeholders, tests, comments, `throw new Error(...)`.
- **Exception:** `src/i18n.js` `MESSAGES.pt` / `MESSAGES.en` for UI copy only.

## Principles

| Principle | Rule |
|---|---|
| **KISS** | Simplest working solution. No premature abstractions. |
| **YAGNI** | No speculative features, TODOs, or unused helpers. |
| **DRY** | One place for tab rules (`decideTabAction`), constants (`config.js`). |
| **SRP** | One reason to change per function/file. SW orchestrates; `rotation.js` computes. |
| **Clean Code** | Meaningful names, small functions, early returns, no nested ternaries. |
| **Testability** | Pure logic without `chrome.*`; inject `fetch` in API layer for tests. |

## Style

### Functions

- **Prefer `const` arrow functions** — not `function` declarations.
- Sync: `const tabMuted = (settings) => …`
- Async: `const fetchLive = async () => …`
- UI handlers: **`handle` prefix** — `const handlePlayClick = async () => …`
- Use `function` only when unavoidable (e.g. hoisting across a tight mutual-recursion pair). Default is `const`.

```javascript
// Good
const tabMuted = (settings) => settings.audio === 'muted';

const handlePlayClick = async () => {
  const state = await send({ type: 'PLAY' });
  if (state?.error) showToast(state.error);
};

// Bad — function keyword, Portuguese, vague name
function mudo(s) { return s.audio === 'muted'; }
const click = async () => { /* ... */ };
```

### Naming (readability)

- **No single-letter variables** in callbacks or business logic.
- Name what the value *is*: `stream`, `login`, `tabId`, `error` — not `s`, `c`, `e`, `n`.
- **`for` loop index only:** `i` / `j` allowed when the loop body is short and index-only.
- **`catch`:** use `error`, not `e`.
- **`map` / `filter` / `forEach`:** name the element (`(stream) => stream.login`, not `(s) => s.login`).
- Prefix `_` only for intentionally unused parameters (e.g. `_live` in a stub).

```javascript
// Good
rotation.channels.filter((login) => liveLogins.has(login));
live.forEach((stream, index) => { /* ... */ });

// Bad
rotation.channels.filter((c) => liveLogins.has(c));
live.forEach((s, i) => { /* ... */ });
```

### Types

- **JavaScript only** — no TypeScript, no build step (see `AGENTS.md`).
- Optional **JSDoc** on exported pure helpers when it clarifies shapes (`@param`, `@returns`).
- Do not add TypeScript or `@ts-check` without an explicit project decision.

### Other

- Empty `catch` only at Chrome API boundaries; prefer a short comment why.
- Guard content script: `globalThis.__smsPlayerActive`.
- Tests: English `describe` / `it` labels; update tests when changing `rotation.js` or `auth.js`.

## Diff discipline

- Smallest correct diff.
- Match existing file patterns.
- Do not refactor unrelated code in the same change.
